So my recommendation would be to:
1. write a `generateRandomGeometricGraphInUnitSquare(int nPoints, float r)` that returns a random geometric `Graph` with the given settings. I would use `JGraphT` to simplify implementation, since it already has a `Graph` class you can use.
2. build a loop that iterates through possible values of `x` and `r`, and for each combination of those values, performs `n` experiments to calculate the probability that a graph with those settings will be connected. If using `JGraphT`, you can know that just by calling [`isConnected`](https://jgrapht.org/javadoc/org.jgrapht.core/org/jgrapht/alg/connectivity/ConnectivityInspector.html#isConnected()) after passing your graph to a `ConnectivityInspector`. Output values that can be plotted using a spreadsheet or any other plotting mechanism of your choice.

